= Results and Discussion

This chapter should present the results of your work, be they in the form of a software product, experimental findings, or both. You should also link these results to your original objectives. For software-oriented projects, how well does it meet your original requirements? Provide data where possible, e.g., results of user testing, performance measures, etc. For research-oriented projects, you should present the data in an appropriate format (tables, charts, visualisations) and discuss what the data shows.
